    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "Eusocial wasp fauna of Sulawesi Island, the central island of Wallacea (Hymenoptera: Vespidae; Polistinae, Vespinae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4304805>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4304803>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296950>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296948> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4304805>
    dc:description "FIGURES 7–16. ♀ of Polistes species. 7–8. P. tenebricosus. 9–10. P. sagittarius. 11–12, 15. P. celebensis. 13–14, 16. P. stigma. 7, 9, 12, 14. Head, frontal view, an arrow in 7 and 9 indicates anterior tentorial pit. 8. First two metasomal segments, lateral view, an arrow indicates basal angle of S1. 10, 11, 13. Habitus, lateral view, 15–16. Hind tarsal claws. Scale line 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4304805/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4304803>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–6. ♀ of Vespa species. 1. V. tropica. 2–3. V. velutina. 4. V. affinis. 5–6. V. fervida. 1–5. Metasoma (1, 3–5. Lateral view, 2. Dorsal view). 6. Head, frontal view, arrows indicate apical teeth." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4304803/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296950>
    dc:description "FIGURES 26–29. Maps showing distribution records of Sulawesian eusocial wasps. 26. Vespa (four species). 27. Polistes (four species). 28. Ropalidiine species non-endemic to Sulawesi I. (five species). 29. Ropalidia species endemic to Sulawesi I. (three species)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4296950/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296948>
    dc:description "FIGURES 17–25. ♀ of Ropalidiini species. 17–18. Parapolybia varia. 19. Ropalidia mathematica. 20–21. R. marginata. 22. R. pilosa. 23. R. impetuosa. 24. R. plebeja. 25. R. celebensis. 17, 19–20, 22–24. Habitus, lateral view. 18. Head, frontal view. 21. Posterior part of mesosoma and T1, dorsal view, an arrow indicates paired basal carina of propodeum. 25. Head, mesosoma and T1, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4296948/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

